{
  "texts": [
    "The connecting lines among these circles, termed \"links, \" represent the connections or relationships between various elements, such as authors, documents, or keywords.",
    "These links can represent co-authorships, co-citations, or co-occurrences of keywords in a bibliometric network.",
    "\"Total Link Strength\" is a metric used in network analysis and refers to the overall strength or significance of connections within a network.",
    "It measures the combined influence or importance of all the links or connections between nodes or entities in a network.",
    "Additionally, citation maps displayed the connections and citations between different partners, with larger circles representing higher citation counts and stronger linkages."
  ]
}